How to run locally

Ensure you have Node.js, npm, git, and an IDE such as VS Code installed.

Node.js and npm install guide: https://nodejs.org/en/download/
Git install: https://git-scm.com/downloads
VS Code install: https://code.visualstudio.com/

---

## Installation and Setup Steps

1. Clone the repository:
   git clone https://github.com/azlannaeem/csc309-a3.git

2. Install frontend dependencies:
   cd frontend
   npm install

3. Install backend dependencies:
   cd ../backend
   npm install

4. Set up Prisma:
   npx prisma generate
   npx prisma db push
   npm run seed # (This command populates the database but you can edit the seed file if needed)

5. Start the backend server:
   node index.js 3000

6. In a new terminal, start the frontend app:
   cd frontend
   npm run dev

You now have a locally running loyalty program application.

---

Deployment Instructions (Using Railway)

1. Create a GitHub repo and push your project there (if not already done).

2. Create a Railway account and sign in with GitHub:
   https://railway.app/

3. Create a new Railway project, and link it to your GitHub repository.

4. Set up the frontend service:
   Click + New → GitHub Repo → Select your repo.
   In the frontend service, set:
   Root Directory: frontend
   Build Command: npm run build
   Start Command: npx serve -s dist
   Deploy and generate a domain.

5. Set up the backend service:
   Add a second service in the same project.
   Set:
   Root Directory: backend
   Start Command: node index.js
   Add an environment variable:
   FRONTEND_URL=https://<your-frontend-domain>
   Deploy and generate a domain.

6. Update frontend .env (locally or on Railway) with:
   VITE_BACKEND_URL=https://<your-backend-domain>

7. Redeploy frontend so it knows the backend URL.

---

## Additional Package Information

-   Multer is used for file uploads
-   qrcode.react is used for QR code generation
